{
  "doc_id": "38107",
  "text": "A wide range of molecular basis encoded in the genomes has been addressed with the progress of technologies in molecular biology. We have focused on the landscape of the mammalian transcriptome and revealed its striking complexity including a substantial population of noncoding RNA and frequently occurring sense/antisense transcription [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Despite these efforts it still remains a major challenge to fully understand the processes responsible for determining the shape of the transcriptome.",
